# Shower.js structure rules

## Shower invariants

- Treat this project as a Shower.js presentation, not as a generic landing page.
- Preserve Shower-compatible slide structure.
- Each slide must remain a separate `<section class="slide">`.
- Do not nest slides inside other slides.
- Do not replace Shower semantics with custom JS-driven slide systems.

## Preferred built-in Shower patterns

- Prefer `.next` for staged reveal of list items or content blocks.
- Prefer `.shout` for short section-divider or emphasis slides only.
- Use Shower-native structure first, then add project-specific classes only when needed.

## Slide composition

- Each slide should represent one clear idea.
- Keep slide markup clean and shallow; avoid unnecessary wrappers.
- Preserve readable HTML structure so slides can be edited manually later.

## Editing discipline

- When adding a new slide, choose one of the approved project slide templates.
- If the request does not clearly match one template, ask which template to use before generating markup.
- Do not invent a brand new slide layout without explicit user approval.

## Images

- Use `<img>` as the default image insertion method.
- Do not restructure the whole slide layout just because an image is added.
- Fit the image into the closest approved template first.
